name: Stanmer Park Orchard
short_description: National Collection of Sussex apples with 31 varieties.
description: Historic orchard in Stanmer Park featuring the National Collection of Sussex apples with 31 different varieties, plus heritage pears and plums. Regular community activity days and apple pressing events in autumn.

name: Racehill Community Orchard
short_description: Over 200 fruit trees planted by the community.
description: Community orchard at Whitehawk with over 200 fruit trees including Sussex apple varieties, pears, plums and cherries. Regular volunteer workdays welcome new members.

name: Bevendean Recreation Ground Orchard
description: Newly established community orchard with 30 fruit trees including apples, pears, plums, cherries and damsons. Free community access for local residents.

name: Brighton Marina Coastal Path
short_description: Coastal foraging for rock samphire and sea kale.
description: Coastal foraging area along Brighton Marina offering rock samphire, sea kale, wild cabbage, plantain and fig trees. Follow sustainable foraging practices.

name: South Downs National Park
short_description: Extensive hedgerow network across the National Park.
description: Multiple hedgerow foraging locations throughout South Downs National Park. Find blackberries, sloes, elderberries, rose hips, hawthorn berries and hazelnuts. Follow the foraging code of conduct.

name: Stanmer Woods
description: Ancient woodland rich in wild garlic (spring), nettles, seasonal mushrooms, elderflower and wild herbs. Proper identification essential for mushroom foraging.

name: Ashdown Forest
short_description: Ancient forest with abundant wild food.
description: Ancient forest offering blackberries, bilberries, chestnuts, mushrooms and elderberries. Practice sustainable picking. Beautiful walking area.

name: Sharnfold Farm
short_description: 40 acres of pick-your-own fruit and vegetables.
description: Large pick-your-own farm with strawberries, raspberries, blackberries, blackcurrants, redcurrants, gooseberries and seasonal vegetables. Farm shop on site.

name: Maynards Farm
short_description: One of UK's longest established PYO farms.
description: Historic pick-your-own farm offering strawberries, apples, cherries, plums, raspberries, blackcurrants, cobnuts and tayberries. Family-run since generations.

name: Tibbs Farm
short_description: Beautiful valley farm with rare fruits.
description: Family-run farm in stunning Tillingham Valley offering strawberries, raspberries, gooseberries, apricots, plums, blackcurrants, tayberries and tummelberries. Cafe with valley views.
tags: pyo, farm, valley, apricots, tayberries, tummelberries

name: Middle Farm
description: Historic working farm with pick-your-own apples, strawberries and raspberries. Features traditional cider press demonstrations and excellent farm shop.

name: Oast Farm
description: Pick-your-own apples, pears, strawberries, raspberries, tayberries, plums, cherries and blackberries. Also sells own eggs and honey.

name: Ockford Farm
short_description: Rent your own fruit tree for the season.
description: 34-acre fruit farm offering rent-a-tree service. Rent apple, pear, cherry or plum trees for the entire growing season and harvest your own fruit.

name: Hollingdean Estate Orchard
short_description: Over 100 fruit trees around the estate.
description: Community orchard featuring over 100 fruit trees including apples, pears, plums, figs and walnuts spread throughout the Hollingdean Estate.

name: Lewes Town Centre
short_description: Historic town with fruit-bearing street trees.
description: Historic market town featuring fruit-bearing street trees including plums, apples and pears. Community picking from street trees in season.

name: Eastbourne Seafront
short_description: Victorian street trees and coastal foraging.
description: Victorian-era planted street trees including fruit varieties, plus coastal foraging opportunities for sea vegetables and samphire along the seafront.

name: Devil's Dyke
description: Dramatic South Downs viewpoint with excellent hedgerow foraging for blackberries, elderberries, sloes, hawthorn berries and wild herbs.

name: Seven Sisters Country Park
short_description: Coastal chalk cliffs with diverse foraging.
description: Iconic white chalk cliffs offering coastal foraging for sea kale, rock samphire, plus hedgerow blackberries, elderberries and wild herbs.

name: Friston Forest
description: Extensive Forestry Commission woodland excellent for autumn foraging. Sweet chestnuts, beechnuts, blackberries and seasonal mushrooms.

name: Bewl Water
description: Large reservoir surrounded by extensive hedgerow network offering blackberries, elderberries, sloes, crab apples and wild plums.

name: Pevensey Levels
description: Historic wetland area with rich hedgerows offering blackberries, sloes, elderberries, samphire and wild plums.

name: Iford Brooks
description: Local nature reserve with good hedgerow access for blackberries, elderberries, sloes, rose hips and crab apples.

name: Seaford Head
description: Dramatic coastal headland offering rock samphire, sea kale, wild cabbage and alexanders. Stunning chalk cliff views.

name: Charleston Farmhouse Gardens
description: Historic garden at Charleston Farmhouse with heritage apple, pear and quince trees. Check access and visiting times.

name: Cuckmere Haven
description: Beautiful river valley meeting the sea. Coastal foraging for samphire and sea vegetables, plus elderberries, blackberries and wild herbs inland.

name: Newhaven Harbour
description: Active working harbour with coastal foraging opportunities for rock samphire, sea beets and sea purslane along quieter areas.

name: Castle Hill Newhaven
description: Historic hill fort with South Downs views. Foraging for wild herbs, elderberries, blackberries and sloes on downland.

name: Brede High Woods
short_description: Ancient woodland with diverse wild food.
description: Ancient woodland offering wild garlic, sweet chestnuts, seasonal mushrooms and hazelnuts. Managed by Sussex Wildlife Trust.
tags: foraging, woodland, ancient, wild-garlic, chestnuts, swt

name: Hastings Country Park
description: Spectacular coastal park combining dramatic cliffs with woodland valleys. Blackberries, elderberries, mushrooms, coastal plants and wild herbs.
tags: foraging, coastal, woodland, cliffs, dramatic, diverse

name: Battle Abbey Woods
description: Historic woodland surrounding the site of the Battle of Hastings. Sweet chestnuts, blackberries, elderberries and seasonal mushrooms.

name: Filching Manor Orchard
description: Small community orchard near historic Filching Manor. Apples, pears and plums available for community picking in autumn.

name: Wealdway Trail
description: Long distance footpath with hedgerow foraging opportunities along 80 miles. Hedgerow fruits, nuts and wild herbs. Follow sustainable foraging guidelines.

description: A community resource for free food, reducing waste and supporting local people.
